Class Complex

  • java.lang.Object
    • aufgabe1_1.Complex

  • public class Complex
extends java.lang.Object
    Complex.

    Represents a complex number Z = a + i*b with real part Re(Z) = a and imaginary part Im(Z) = b.

    Version:
    2013-10-16
    Author:
    Jendrik Baggendorf, Daniel Dahmer

      • add

        public Complex add(Complex z)
        Addition with a complex number.

        For Z1 = a + i*b and Z2 = c + i*d:
        Z1 + Z2 = (a + i*b) + (c + i*d) = (a + c) + i * (b + d)

        Parameters:
        z - Complex number to add with
        Returns:
        reference of this object after addition

      • sub

        public Complex sub(Complex z)
        Subtraction with a complex number.

        For Z1 = a + i*b and Z2 = c + i*d:
        Z1 - Z2 = (a + i*b) - (c + i*d) = (a - c) + i * (b - d)

        Parameters:
        z - Complex number to subtract with
        Returns:
        reference of this object after subtraction

      • mul

        public Complex mul(Complex z)
        Multiply with a complex number.

        For Z1 = a + i*b and Z2 = c + i*d:
        Z1 * Z2 = (a + i*b) * (c + i*d) = (ac - bd) + i * (ad + bc)

        Parameters:
        z - Complex number to multiply with
        Returns:
        reference of this object after multiplication

      • div

        public Complex div(Complex z)
        Division with a complex number.

        For Z1 = a + i*b and Z2 = c + i*d:
        Z1 / Z2 = [(ac + bd) / (c² + d²)] + i * [(cb - ad) / (c² + d²)]

        Parameters:
        z - Complex number to divide with
        Returns:
        reference of this object after division

        public java.lang.String toString()
